I see there has been some confusion caused by a faulty upload of message
#1 in the database. to reiterate (and mis-spell!) as much as possible
without complete redundancy:

For Jewelers, Weavers, Bowyers:
1 special order per 2 weeks at rank 20
2 per 2 weeks at rank 25
3 per 2 weeks at rank 30 (Mastery)
+1 per 2 weeks for each FULL 10 levels over 30 (4@40, 5@50, etc)

For Weaponsmiths:
Same as above, but you get specials every 4 weeeks, not every 2. This is
mostly because of the IN GAME impact weapons have, more than anything
else. Please note that you CAN modify armor for the time being, the
rules may change and I will post them then.

For Alchemists:
The partial line about free components WAS deleted but somehow stuck
around. That is NOT being done at this time. I am contemplating a few
things, but it will take a little while to work something out.

For Miners:
I honestly haven't got any ideas for what would be useful for you to
have because of your skills in mining. What I *might* do is this:
You will be allowed to give your metals to me for sale to other PC
crafters as they need them. A flat charge based on metal type will be
set for all metals you give me (so keep the ones you want to extort
money out of people if they want them) Also note: These metals are for
use in crafting NON-weapons ONLY. Weapons MUST be crafted in game by the
actual metal you have mined, I cannot reproduce it. I will track the
number & kind of metals given to me and pay you on a bi-weekly or montly
basis, depending on amount of metals sold. Your other option is to sell
them directly to me at 1/2 value I would sell them to PC crafters at &
you would get the cash instantly. These metals will be absorbed by the
NPC crafters of the city and not available for resale. What do you
think? Post on Topic #5 (Ideas & Things).

-Morthain Da'Karian

(Note I will post a schedule for when orders will be delivered as soon
as I get a decent wall calendar. This MAY mean you will loose a order
set and I appologize in advance, but I need ALL crafters on the same
schedule or I will go nuts trying to keep track of who gets what when.)

